Defendant Shawntel Denise Hayes in court with attorney Mark Allan Dluzak.  Taylor L. Kraus appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Deputy Court Clerk ssm.  Court found the state has satisfied victims' rights law.  Sentencing proceeded.  Statements by the State, defense and defendant.  Defendant sentenced to serve 6 months in the House of Correction with credit for 2 days time served.  Court STAYED the sentence and placed defendant on Probation with the State of Wisconsin, Department of Corrections for a period of 12 months.
Conditions:
*  AODA assessment/treatment deemed appropriate;
*  Pay costs and surcharges or, if not paid, convert to a civil judgment;
*  Submit a DNA sample and pay the DNA surcharge.
Notice of Right to Seek Postconviction Relief received and filed.
